===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[رمضان]]}} ({{IPAchar|ramaɖáːn}}, ninth month of the [[Muslim]] calendar), from {{ARchar|[[ارتمض]]}} ({{IPAchar|irtámaɖa}}, "to be consumed by grief and sorrow").

===Proper noun===
'''Ramadan'''

# the [[holy]] ninth [[month]] of the [[Islamic]] [[lunar]] [[calendar]] (the [[Hijra]]), during which [[Muslim]]s [[fast]] between [[sunrise]] and [[sunset]]; they also refrain from [[smoking]] and [[sexual]] [[relation]]s.

